Use this README file to introduce your application and point to useful places in the API for learning more.
Run "rake doc:app" to generate API documentation for your models, controllers, helpers, and libraries.

Postgres Notes

add these to database.yml

development:
  adapter: postgresql
  host: localhost
  database: stocko_dev
  username: stocko
  password: stocko
  

Install pg gem

sudo bash
export ARCHFLAGS='-arch i386'; gem install pg


StockPrice, MarketData, Array(of stock price or market data) custom methods
up? <=> close > open
down? <=> close < open
change <=> (close - open)/open
max_change <=> (high - low)/open
next(days = 1) <=> StockPrice of next 1 or N days
prev(days = 1) <=> StockPrice of prev 1 or N days

Array(of stock price or market data) custom methods
volume(average), high, low, open, close, start_date, end_date 
stock_array?
stock_price_array?
market_data_array?